TASK 1: Real Estate Property List
Topic: Handling Large Numbers & Commission Logic. Scenario: You are working for a Property Dealer in DHA/Bahria Town. Create a sales sheet for 25 Properties.
1. Data Entry (25 Unique Rows):
Columns: Property ID, Location (e.g., Phase 1, Phase 6, Clifton, Gulshan), Type (House, Flat, Plot), Area (Sq Yards), Price per Sq Yard.
Requirement:
Enter 25 unique properties.
Area should be between 120 and 1000.
Price per Sq Yard should be realistic (e.g., 50,000 to 200,000).
2. Calculation Tasks:
Total Property Price: Create a column Total Value.
Logic: Area multiplied by Price per Sq Yard.
Agent Commission (2%): Create a column Agent Fee.
Logic: Calculate 2% of the Total Value.
Formatting: Apply the Comma Style (1,000,000) to all price columns so zeros are easy to read. (Home Tab > Number Section > Comma Icon).
3. Logic Task (IF Formula):
Category: Create a column Category.
Logic: If Total Value is greater than 20,000,000 (2 Crore), display "Luxury". Otherwise, display "Standard".

TASK 2: Hotel Booking Management
Topic: Service Charges, Tax & Conditional Logic. Scenario: You are the Front Desk Manager at a 5-Star Hotel. Calculate the bills for 25 Guests.
1. Data Entry (25 Unique Rows):
Columns: Guest Name, Room Type (Standard, Deluxe, Suite), Nights Stayed, Rate Per Night.
Requirement:
Nights Stayed: Random numbers between 1 and 15.
Rate Per Night: Standard (10,000), Deluxe (25,000), Suite (50,000).
2. Calculation Tasks:
Room Charges: Create a column Room Cost.
Logic: Nights Stayed multiplied by Rate Per Night.
Service Tax (13%): Create a column Tax Amount.
Logic: Calculate 13% of Room Cost.
Final Bill: Create a column Total Payable.
Logic: Room Cost + Tax Amount.
3. Visualization & Logic:
VIP Status: Create a column Customer Type.
Logic: If Nights Stayed is greater than 7, display "VIP", otherwise "Regular".
Chart: Create a Column Chart showing Guest Name and Total Payable to see who paid the most.

  
